methods.notes: The IsoPlayer.instance thread-safe invoke.   Calls the supplied callback if the IsoPlayer.instance is non-null.   Performs this in a thread-safe manner.    It is intended that, should any thread intend to use the IsoPlayer.instance, and does not want another thread   to change the ptr in the meanwhile, it should call invokeOnPlayerInstance(Runnable callback)    eg.   IsoPlayer.invokeOnPlayerInstance(()->     {         IsoPlayer.instance.doStuff();     }
methods.name: invokeOnPlayerInstance
